				 ING Vysya capital base to rise
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Nov. 27: ING Vysya Life Insurance Company will shore up its capital base by Rs 150 crore before March 2008 to support the companys growth plans. City-based Exide Industries is the largest shareholder with a 50 per cent stake in the company.																								The Netherlands-based ING Insurance International BV holds a 26 per cent stake, while Gujarat Ambuja Cements has 14.8 per cent and Enam Securities, 9.2 per cent.																								The companys equity base was Rs 790 crore as on October 30 this year. 																								We are looking at a fresh capital infusion of Rs 150 crore during the first quarter of next year, said Rajeev Kanal, associate vice-president (product development), ING Vysya Life Insurance Company Ltd. 																								The insurer, which launched its eighth unit-linked plan, Creating Star, today, is targeting a premium income of Rs 1,068 crore this year compared with Rs 613 crore in 2006. 																								Of the total premium income, we expect Rs 635 crore to come from sales of new policies and the rest will be renewals, Kanal said. 
